In this statement, President Obama sends his warm wishes to those celebrating Hanukkah around the world. He highlights the story of the Maccabees who fought for their freedom and the miracle of the oil lasting for eight nights. He emphasizes that Hanukkah is a time to celebrate Jewish faith and customs but also an opportunity for people of all faiths to come together and recognize our shared aspirations. The President encourages gratitude for our blessings and compassion for those who are suffering, and he calls for a commitment to building a better world for everyone. He concludes by sending his wishes for a joyful Hanukkah to the Jewish community worldwide.